{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Soak bread in water then squeeze dry and set aside.","Place parsley in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>.","Add onions and oil then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <nobr>5 min\/120°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add reserved soaked and drained bread, egg, mustard, paprika, salt, pepper and beef mince then mix <nobr>30 sec\/\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Divide mixture into 6 balls,  place a piece of Cheddar in centre and enclose burger mince around cheese so cheese is not visible. Flatten to form burgers (Ø 9 cm) and transfer to a plate, then refrigerate for 20 minutes.","Heat oil in a large frying pan. Cook burgers over a medium heat for 4-5 minutes on each side until cooked through. Allow burgers  to stand in frying pan, off the heat, for 2-3 minutes to allow cheese to firm up a little. Serve in a bun of your choice."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 slices sliced white bread (approx. 95 g)","water, for soaking","5 g fresh parsley leaves","130 g red onions, quartered","20 g sunflower oil, plus 1 tsp for frying","1 medium egg","½ Tbsp English mustard, or to taste","1 tsp hot paprika","1 tsp fine sea salt","½ tsp ground pepper","500 g beef mince, broken in pieces","120 g Cheddar cheese, in 6 pieces (4 cm x 4 cm x 1 cm)"]}],"id":"r102072","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-yzQKOWRkrf4\/XZQv4z76JwI\/AAAAAAAAcgw\/unjQFTxAnHQQEQa4ZVd5IwwQz7yVOMIewCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_PKmkj6JGY84FAeJm.png","title":"Beef Burger with Melting Cheese Centre","publishedAt":"2016-08-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"23.4 g","fat":"30.8 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"9.2 g","calories":"1703 kJ \/ 407 kcal"},"usefulItems":"frying pan, refrigerator, hob","hintsAndTricks":["Serving suggestion: grill burger buns in the oven or toaster, so they are crispy. Serve with ketchup or avocado mayonnaise, lettuce, coleslaw or pickles.","Feta also works well instead of Cheddar."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","45m","6 portions"]}